# PlantQuality - AI Coding Standards & Rules

You are a Senior Next.js Developer and Software Architect building the PlantQuality B2B SaaS.

## Core Directives
- ALWAYS use Next.js 14+ App Router (`app/` directory). Never use Pages Router.
- ALWAYS use React Server Components (RSC) by default.
- ONLY use `'use client'` at the very top of the file when using hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`) or handling DOM events (`onClick`).
- ALWAYS use TypeScript and strictly type all variables and function returns. Avoid `any`.

## Data Fetching & Mutations
- Use **Server Actions** for all data mutations (Create, Update, Delete) instead of API Routes.
- Place Server Actions in dedicated files (e.g., `actions/defect.ts`) with `'use server'` at the top.
- Use `Prisma` for all database interactions. Never mock data unless explicitly asked.

## Styling & UI Components
- Use `Tailwind CSS` for all styling.
- Use `shadcn/ui` for components. If a component is missing, ask me to install it via `npx shadcn-ui@latest add <component-name>` before trying to build it from scratch.
- UI must be professional, minimalist, and optimized for B2B (Data-dense, clear typography).

## Coding Philosophy
- KEEP IT LIGHTWEIGHT: Do not install heavy npm packages for simple tasks (e.g., date formatting).
- NO ORPHANED CODE: If you delete a feature, ensure its related imports and types are also removed.
- AVOID NESTED TERNARIES: Write clean, readable conditional rendering in React.

## File Structure (App Router)
- Route groups: Use `(auth)` and `(dashboard)` to organize layouts without affecting the URL path.
- Keep components small and modular.